# Project-Specific Conventions

This rule adapts the shared engineering framework to this specific repository.

Project-specific engineering decisions are defined in:

`docs/project/ENGINEERING.md`

Follow that document whenever project-specific conventions are required.

Do not duplicate engineering decisions here.

---

# Purpose

Use this rule to remind the agent that project-specific engineering conventions override generic defaults.

Examples include:

* language version;
* dependency management;
* repository layout;
* runtime technologies;
* testing strategy;
* validation commands;
* coding conventions;
* deployment assumptions.

The authoritative source remains `ENGINEERING.md`.

---

# When ENGINEERING.md Exists

Treat `ENGINEERING.md` as authoritative for:

* language and runtime versions;
* package management;
* repository structure;
* project technology stack;
* configuration strategy;
* coding conventions;
* validation workflow;
* operational assumptions.

Do not invent engineering conventions that are not documented.

---

# Local Cursor Guidance

Only place Cursor-specific guidance here when it cannot reasonably belong in the framework.

Examples:

* repository-specific prompting hints;
* preferred repository navigation;
* editor-specific workflow adjustments.

Avoid duplicating framework documentation.

Avoid duplicating project documentation.

---

# General Rule

Framework rules define **how engineering is performed**.

`ENGINEERING.md` defines **how this project is engineered**.

This file only bridges the framework to Cursor.
